Two changes to the Layer 2 explorer before I run it on a real app:
Add a termination_reason field to the run output, with two values: "frontier_exhausted" (ran out of new actions to try — map is complete) vs "budget_exhausted" (hit the action cap — map is incomplete). Also raise the default action budget to 500.
Make return-to-state reuse the saved auth session. The reload-based recovery must reuse the persisted storage_state/cookies so a reload re-lands authenticated, never on a login page. If a reload lands on a login/SSO page, treat it as a return_to_state_failure and log it rather than continuing.
